    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Implement missing find_gscn_to_scan function for NR synchronization\n\n### Summary\nThe `find_gscn_to_scan` function was referenced in the codebase but never implemented, causing undefined behavior when trying to determine GSCN (Global Synchronization Channel Number) values for NR cell search. This function is critical for UE synchronization as it provides the list of GSCN values that need to be scanned for a given frequency band and subcarrier spacing.\n\nWhen users attempted to call `find_gscn_to_scan()`, their application would either fail to link or crash at runtime due to the missing implementation. The function is now properly implemented in `nr_common.c` with a corresponding declaration in `nr_common.h`.\n\nThe implementation includes the complete synchronization raster table data from 3GPP TS 38.101-1/2 Table 5.4.3.3-1, supporting all defined NR bands and subcarrier spacing combinations. It correctly handles different step sizes for various band/SCS pairs and respects the maximum GSCN count parameter.\n\n### Changes\n- `common/utils/nr/nr_common.h`: Added function declaration for `find_gscn_to_scan`\n- `common/utils/nr/nr_common.c`: Implemented `find_gscn_to_scan` function with full sync raster table\n- The function returns the number of GSCN values found or -1 for invalid band/SCS combinations\n- Properly handles step sizes greater than 1 (e.g., Band 79 with SCS 1 uses step size 16)\n- Respects the `max_gscn` parameter to limit returned values\n\n"
}